18.21	Helmet_for_My_Pillow	Helmet for My Pillow	Helmet for My Pillow is the personal narrative written by World War II United States Marine Corps veteran, author and military historian Robert Leckie. First published in 1957, the story begins with Leckie enlisting in the United States Marines shortly after the 1941 Attack on Pearl Harbor.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/b/bc/Helmet_for_my_pillow.jpg
